 ("nm0097648", null, "1894-4-23", "Salt Lake City, Utah, USA", "cancer", "1962-6-19", "Hollywood, Los Angeles, California, USA", "5' 10½\" (1.79 m)", "Frank Borzage was born on April 23, 1894 in Salt Lake City, Utah, USA. He was an actor and director, known for Bad Girl (1931), 7th Heaven (1927) and No Greater Glory (1934). He was married to Juanita Scott, Edna Skelton and Rena Rogers. He died on June 19, 1962 in Hollywood, Los Angeles, California, USA.", null, null, "Frank", null, "Borzage", null, null, "Frank Borzage"),
